## Best Practices

### Story Mapping
- Start with user activities (the backbone)
- Keep the map visual and collaborative
- Prioritize ruthlessly (VS1 must-have vs. VS2+ nice-to-have)
- Ensure VS1 (walking skeleton) delivers end-to-end value
- Use named value slices with measurable goals

### Value Slices
- VS1 = Core workflow, essential compliance, basic functionality
- VS2 = Efficiency improvements, bulk actions, shortcuts
- VS3 = Enhanced experience, personalization, advanced features
- Each slice has a clear, measurable goal
- Name each slice descriptively (not "MVP", "Phase 2")

### Story Map Documents
- Save to `docs/story-maps/` for reference
- Include visualization (text-based table)
- Link to epic and PRD
- Show story counts per value slice
- Present clearly for PM review

## Anti-Patterns to Avoid

- ❌ Generic value slices ("MVP", "Phase 2", "Nice-to-have")
- ❌ Value slices without measurable goals
- ❌ Skipping HUMAN-IN-THE-LOOP approval
- ❌ Technical tasks instead of user activities
- ❌ Too many activities (>10) or too few (<3)
- ❌ VS1 that doesn't deliver end-to-end value
- ❌ Creating stories without story mapping first

